comment: Carroll (ATL) establishes himself in the direct path of James (CLE) before the contact occurs.
Thompson's (CLE) contact does not affect Teague's (ATL) shot.
Bazemore (ATL) bumps James (CLE) and hits his arm as he is rebounding, causing him to lose his balance.
James (CLE) does not prevent Millsap (ATL) from freely moving.
Teague (ATL) is in legal guarding position when James (CLE) attempts to jump/slip by him.
Carroll (ATL) trips Shumpert (CLE) and causes him to go to the floor.
James (CLE) does not go through Carroll (ATL).
Scott (ATL) does not push off of Shumpert (CLE).
Smith (CLE) cleanly blocks Carroll's (ATL) shot.
Scott (ATL) engages Thompson (CLE) but does not prevent him from attempting to retrieve the rebound.
James (CLE) makes contact with Teague's (ATL) body and the contact affects his shot.
Scott (ATL) makes contact with Thompson's (CLE) body and the contact affects his shot.
Contact by James (CLE) on Bazemore (ATL) is incidental in their attempt to secure the rebound.
Mack (ATL) cleanly strips the ball from James (CLE).
Dellavedova (CLE) makes contact with Teague's (ATL) body and the contact affects his shot.
Millsap's (ATL) contact does not affect James' (CLE) shot.
Teague's (ATL) contact on Smith (CLE) is incidental in their attempt to secure the rebound.
Bazemore (ATL) holds Thompson (CLE) affecting his FOM.
Mack's (ATL) contact on Thompson (CLE) is incidental in their attempt to secure the rebound.
Thompson (CLE) and Scott (ATL) engage under the rim in attempt to secure the rebound.
James (CLE) does not make contact with Teague's (ATL) arm.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials determined that the ball went out of bounds with :31.3 seconds on the clock.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Carroll (ATL) was the last player to touch the ball was upheld and CLE was awarded possession.
Millsap's (ATL) contact with James (CLE) on shot is incidental to his attempt to defend.
Millsap (ATL) and Thompson (CLE) engage before rebound is secured.
